# Environment Configuration for Service Report Backend

## Development Environment (.env.example)

Copy this file to `.env` and update with your configuration.

```env
# Application
NODE_ENV=development
PORT=3000
APP_NAME=Service Report API

# Database
DB_HOST=localhost
DB_PORT=5432
DB_NAME=service_report
DB_USER=postgres
DB_PASSWORD=postgres
DB_POOL_MIN=2
DB_POOL_MAX=10

# CORS
CORS_ORIGIN=http://localhost:4200

# JWT (Future Authentication)
JWT_SECRET=your_super_secret_jwt_key_change_this_in_production
JWT_EXPIRE=7d

# Logging
LOG_LEVEL=debug
LOG_FORMAT=json

# Features
ENABLE_CORS=true
ENABLE_DEVICE_MANAGEMENT=true
ENABLE_SERVICE_REPORTS=true

# API Documentation
ENABLE_SWAGGER=true
SWAGGER_URL=/api/docs

# Email (Future)
MAIL_HOST=smtp.example.com
MAIL_PORT=587
MAIL_USER=your-email@example.com
MAIL_PASSWORD=your-password
MAIL_FROM=noreply@service-report.com

# File Upload (Future)
MAX_FILE_SIZE=10485760
UPLOAD_DIR=./uploads
ALLOWED_FILE_TYPES=pdf,jpg,jpeg,png,xlsx,csv

# Timezone
TIMEZONE=UTC

# Version
API_VERSION=1.0.0
